209 "  In other words \"How did Maple interpret command  2(3+4)?\"  Or
, alternately, why is this particular example in the built-in function
s section?   To answer this, try some more examples like 2(7), 2(34), \+
2(t). " }{TEXT 283 131 "Maple interpreted p as 2 times 1--TREATS IT AS
 A CONSTANT--DOESN'T SEE WHAT IS IN PARENTHESES--NO MULTIPLICATION COM
MAND WAS GIVEN " }{TEXT -1 3 "   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
