{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "4.  Prime Numbers.  A " }{TEXT 281 12 "pr
ime number" }{TEXT -1 38 " is an integer (greater than 1 -- why " }
{TEXT 258 12 "greater than" }{TEXT -1 124 " 1?) for which the only (po
sitive integer) factors are 1 and itself.  Examples of prime numbers a
re: 2, 13, 101, 20110771.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "The Maple command " }{TEXT 259 7 "isprime" }
{TEXT -1 58 " determines whether or not a given integer is prime.  Use
 " }{TEXT 260 7 "isprime" }{TEXT -1 105 " it to determine whether  the
 following numbers are prime:  29,  35,  1537,  your ss#,   10!+1,  32
9891. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "isprime(29);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%%tru
eG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "isprime(35);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%&falseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "isprime(1537);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%&f
alseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 19 "isprime(452085169)
;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%%trueG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "isprime(10!+1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 
"6#%&falseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "isprime(3298
91);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%%trueG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 50 "Find all of the prime num
bers between 0 and 200.  " }{TEXT 277 4 "Note" }{TEXT -1 63 ":  It wil
l be helpful for you to review the information in the " }{TEXT 263 11 
"programming" }{TEXT -1 15 " worksheet on  " }{TEXT 264 9 "for loops" 
}{TEXT -1 6 " and  " }{TEXT 265 13 "if statements" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
19 "for i from 0 to 200" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "do if is
prime(i)" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "then print (i); end if;
 od;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"#" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
