{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 386 "When the Digits value was changed, the values of ans_exa
ct and ans_approx were not changed.  If they were not changed, then wh
y are the values diff_10 and diff_100 different?  What is Maple doing \+
different when Digits = 10 as compared to Digits = 100, so that diff_1
0 and diff_100 are different?  (The point of this question is to verba
lly clarify what floating point arithmetic means.)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 120 "DIFF=10 MEANS 10 SIGNIFICANT FIGURES AND DIFF=100 MEANS THERE \+
IS 100 SIGNIFICANT FIGURES--YOU SET THE NUMBER OF SIG FIGS" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 289 2 "kp
" }{TEXT -1 58 "  Okay, but why were diff_10 and diff_100 different?  \+
-1/2" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}{TEXT 290 2 "kp" }{TEXT -1 2 "  " }{TEXT 291 7 "18.5/20" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 164 "diff10 and diff10
0 were different because diff 10 only has 10 significant figures and d
iff 100 has 100 significant figures.  The rest will be seen as zero by
 Maplw." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }{TEXT 292 2 "kp" }{TEXT -1 32 "  say it to me in words in class" }
